🧠 LIME (Local Interpretations)
Provides intuitive breakdown for a single prediction.

Shows which features increased or decreased a specific house's price.

SHAP offers the best unambiguity (9/10) and consistent global explanations but has a high fidelity score (192.4B) and moderate interpretability (7/10).
LIME provides the best fidelity (7.35B) with good interpretability (8/10) and decent unambiguity (7/10).
IML (Interactive Model) isn't directly measurable for fidelity, but excels in interpretability (9/10) while scoring lower on unambiguity (5/10).

SHAP offers the most consistent global explanations.

LIME provides the best fidelity for individual predictions.

IML (interactive model with sliders) is easiest for human interpretation.

